      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>15 threads, <a href=item.html?item=1118&start=0>1</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></form><ul><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100922067141795></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100922067141795><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1118&mid=100922067141795>What is the spawn rate of Giant Spider?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1118&mid=100922067141795#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=110453><span id= >Ardnahoy</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>13 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 24th 2:04 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I usually hang around the heart spider room in UGuk for a few minutes hoping to catch a Giant heart spider and upgrade my Velium Shield.  I don't hang around there too long cuz Guk is a looter's paradise, and I can't stand being in the same room too long especially when I can afford to buy 100 of these shields.  But, my question is, what the hell is the spawn rate of the GIANT spiders?  I've been here for three spawn rates at a time (killed every freaking spider in the joint), and only caught a glimpse of three or four &quot;large&quot; spiders.  Will I see a giant spider, say once per hour?  Anyone know?<br><br>Oh, and just a few tips for all you paladins out there:  Only fight undead.  Go to Luclin and buy the first three spells for Pallies (lvl 9, 15 and 30 spells).  Spook the Dead costs 5 mana... and is our most underused spell.  Imagine this:  cast the lvl 30 Luclin spell (which makes ANY weapon proc a 225dd vs undead), use a shield and ghoulbane.  Fight up to 5 undead blues/whites at a time.  How?  Fear the one you are fighting.  Switch to a new mob then fear it after 10 seconds.  Repeat until all but one mob is on you.  Repeat when the first feared mob returns.  Undead ping-pong.  Wheee!<br><br>Oh, and when GB and your Luclin spell procs, undead don't last very long.<br><br>Want to make your fights less harmful?  Cast the lvl 15 luclin spell (Desist - 2.5 second stun, 15 mana), run behind the mob a'la a rogue and imediately Bash it.  Another 2.5 second stun.<br><br>If you are a paladin and you do not use and perfect these techniques, then you are not getting the best of your character.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ardnahoy<br>Noble Paladin of the 33rd Court of Knights<br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
