<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100787455880339></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100787455880339><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=1118&mid=100787455880339>Level 20?</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=1118&mid=100787455880339#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=84722><span id= >ktadema</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>8 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 9th 12:09 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I camped the Heart Spiders about a week ago for about a total of 4 hours over two days.  During that time, I saw 3 giant spiders.  Of the 3 I got two of these shields and one Chitin Shell Armor drop.  Not too bad really....  The point I want to make is that I used my 25th level ogre SK to camp this.  And he died twice during the camp.  If you aren't careful to conn the other spiders, they may join in and give you a fight with 3-4 spiders.  A GROUP of level 20s can probably take this camp, but as far as soloing is concerned, unless you are twinked up pretty good, I don't see how you can take it before 24.  25 was a pretty good struggle, I promise you that.  I did make some good money selling the spider silks though...and along with getting some good armor, for the time that I spent, I thought it was the best camp I had ever done by myself.  I came away with about 9 stacks of spider silk, a nice shield and BP that I am very proud of.  <br>&nbsp;<br>*** Givins, Erudite Wizard, Rodcet Nife ***<br>***Izzek, Ogre Shadow Knight, Rodcet Nife***</td></tr>
