	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 12th 4:25 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I lvl 20 now, and what sucks (or maybe not) is that I cannot dual wield being a Paladin.  So instead of hitting for 20 or so every 3 seconds i hit for 20, bash for 10, hit for 20 3 seconds after the first hit, and bash again 5 seconds after the first bash.  Bashing delay is so horrible!  Can you imagine if the delay was the same as sword!  The monster would be lucky to NOT be stunned.  So, while not hitting for 20 or so, it bashes the enemy... this is good for not one, or two, but 3 ways.  It acts as a spell interrupter, it also takes away one round of attack for the monster, and it also makes the monster stop running from you (I dont know about the higher level monsters, but if I bash a mob when they're walking a way from a long battle, they stop in place for a couple of seconds).  So, that spell it interrupted could have in some cases saved you 75hp damage from a Orc Priest or some other caster, that stun it gave to the monster will not allow him to attack for a couple of seconds meaning free hits for yourself or free heal during battle, and those bashes that you give to the mob while they walking away from you keeps them still preventing others from joining him in battle.  So, while its not as strong as another sword, it saves you from casting mobs (by interrupting their spells), from malee mobs (by stunning them), and does something like a "mini root" when they start to walk away.  My 2cp.  See you in the Lake of Omen<br>&nbsp;<br>Lamini - Lvl 50 Human Paladin Of Cazic Thule</td></tr>
