	   <tr><td colspan=2>The poison resistance can actually be very useful in specific situations.<br>One that comes to mind is the level 25 fungus mutant in upper guk, which is camped to get components for the paw of opolla.  He casts a nasty "Clockwork Poison" that makes you spin in place for a few seconds, unable to do anything.  Between the chitin shell shield and a couple other items, plus my endure poison spell, I had boosted my poison resist to over 60.  In the 10 hours or so I spent hunting the fungus mutant, I don't think he ever managed to make Clockwork Poison stick more than once in a fight.  Instead he wasted all his time trying to cast a spell that I kept resisting, so he was a rather easy kill.  (I was a low 30's druid at the time.)<br><br>Even now I keep this shield in the bank in case I get a chance to join a raid on the poison dragon Trakanon.<br><br>I underestimated the importance of resists for a long time.  Now I wear a lot of my resist gear fulltime (though it does focus on magic/fire/cold).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
